// ============================================================
// Dependencies E — (A, B) means A depends on B
// ============================================================

// Consumers choose via labels and retail
Consumer->Consumer Purchase Decision
Consumer Purchase Decision->Food Retail Shelf
Consumer Purchase Decision->On-Pack Eco-Label
Consumer Purchase Decision->Carbon / Climate Label
Food Retail Shelf->Farm Output (Produce / Grain / Livestock)
Food Retail Shelf->Retailer Sourcing Standard
Food Retail Shelf->Supply-Chain Traceability

// Retailer standards pull from certification and traceability
Retailer Sourcing Standard->Certification Body (Organic / Regen)
Retailer Sourcing Standard->Supply-Chain Traceability
On-Pack Eco-Label->Certification Body (Organic / Regen)
Carbon / Climate Label->Soil Carbon Measurement
Carbon / Climate Label->Outcome-Based Grading Schema

// Certification depends on measurement and grading
Certification Body (Organic / Regen)->Outcome-Based Grading Schema
Certification Body (Organic / Regen)->Supply-Chain Traceability
Supply-Chain Traceability->Remote Sensing / Satellite MRV
Supply-Chain Traceability->Farm Management Software

// Farmer's output flows from chosen practices
Farmer->Farm Output (Produce / Grain / Livestock)
Farm Output (Produce / Grain / Livestock)->Extractive Industrial Practice
Farm Output (Produce / Grain / Livestock)->Crop Rotation
Farm Output (Produce / Grain / Livestock)->Cover Cropping
Farm Output (Produce / Grain / Livestock)->Crop Diversity / Intercropping
Farm Output (Produce / Grain / Livestock)->No-Till / Reduced Till
Farm Output (Produce / Grain / Livestock)->Integrated Livestock Grazing
Farm Output (Produce / Grain / Livestock)->Agroforestry
Farm Output (Produce / Grain / Livestock)->Monoculture Cropping

// Extractive practice locks into petrochemical stack
Extractive Industrial Practice->Monoculture Cropping
Extractive Industrial Practice->Synthetic Fertiliser (N-P-K)
Extractive Industrial Practice->Pesticides / Herbicides
Monoculture Cropping->Synthetic Fertiliser (N-P-K)
Monoculture Cropping->Pesticides / Herbicides
Monoculture Cropping->Soil Substrate
Synthetic Fertiliser (N-P-K)->Petrochemical Feedstocks
Pesticides / Herbicides->Petrochemical Feedstocks
Petrochemical Feedstocks->Fossil Fuel Energy

// Regenerative practices tap the biological energy matrix
Crop Rotation->Soil Substrate
Crop Rotation->Regen Ag Knowledge (Agronomy)
Cover Cropping->Soil Substrate
Cover Cropping->Regen Ag Knowledge (Agronomy)
Crop Diversity / Intercropping->Soil Microbial Community
Crop Diversity / Intercropping->Regen Ag Knowledge (Agronomy)
No-Till / Reduced Till->Soil Microbial Community
No-Till / Reduced Till->Soil Substrate
Integrated Livestock Grazing->Soil Substrate
Integrated Livestock Grazing->Biodiversity / Pollinators
Agroforestry->Photosynthesis
Agroforestry->Biodiversity / Pollinators
Agroforestry->Water Cycle / Watershed

// Soil biology and photosynthesis as the real energy matrix
Soil Substrate->Soil Microbial Community
Soil Microbial Community->Mycorrhizal Networks
Soil Microbial Community->Photosynthesis
Mycorrhizal Networks->Photosynthesis

// Measurement stack
Soil Carbon Measurement->Soil Microbiology Science
Soil Carbon Measurement->Remote Sensing / Satellite MRV
Outcome-Based Grading Schema->Soil Carbon Measurement
Outcome-Based Grading Schema->Regen Ag Knowledge (Agronomy)
Regen Ag Knowledge (Agronomy)->Soil Microbiology Science
Farm Management Software->Remote Sensing / Satellite MRV

// Policy and treaties
National Government->Policy Levers (Subsidies / Taxes)
Policy Levers (Subsidies / Taxes)->National Farm Payment Scheme (e.g. ELM, CAP reform)
National Farm Payment Scheme (e.g. ELM, CAP reform)->Outcome-Based Grading Schema
Supranational Body (UN / FAO / IPCC)->Climate Treaty (Paris / UNFCCC COP27)
Supranational Body (UN / FAO / IPCC)->Biodiversity Treaty (CBD / Kunming-Montreal draft)
Policy Levers (Subsidies / Taxes)->Climate Treaty (Paris / UNFCCC COP27)
Policy Levers (Subsidies / Taxes)->Biodiversity Treaty (CBD / Kunming-Montreal draft)
Policy Levers (Subsidies / Taxes)->Land Tenure / Property Rights

// Farmer incentive routes
Farmer->National Farm Payment Scheme (e.g. ELM, CAP reform)
Farmer->Regen Ag Knowledge (Agronomy)
Farmer->Land Tenure / Property Rights

